<HEADLINE>
KEALY HAS SUPPORTER ON NOTRE DAME SIDE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN AND BOB YOUNG  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, Ariz. - ASU quarterback  &UR; Ryan Kealy didn't have many
supporters in Sun Devil Stadium by the end of his team's 28-9 loss
to Notre Dame. But he did have one on the Notre Dame sideline.
</P>
<P>
   Irish kicker  &UR; Jim Sanson, a former St. Mary's High School
teammate of Kealy, came to his defense after Kealy was booed by the
crowd and replaced by redshirt freshman  &UR; Chad Elliott.
</P>
<P>
   Sanson spoke with Kealy before the two teams left the field.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just told him to keep his head up,'' Sanson said. ``He's a
great quarterback. He's better than the guy they put in behind him.
I just can't believe they booed him like that.''
</P>
<P>
   Sanson knows what it's like to have the home fans on his back.
He even got death threats after missing an extra point against
Southern California two seasons ago. &QL; 
Grey matter &QL; 
Arizona State center  &UR; Grey Ruegamer is one of 12 finalists
announced Saturday for the Lombardi Award, given to the nation's
top college lineman.
</P>
<P>
   Four nominees are from the Big Ten, including Ohio State's  &UR; Andy
 &UR; Katzenmoyer, who was a finalist last season. Iowa defensive tackle
 &UR; Jared DeVries, Wisconsin offensive tackle  &UR; Aaron Gibson and
Michigan offensive tackle  &UR; John Jansen also are finalists.
</P>
<P>
   UCLA offensive tackle  &UR; Kris Farris is the Pac-10's other
representative. Three come from the Southeastern Conference:
defensive tackle  &UR; Ed Chester, of Florida; linebacker  &UR; Jevon Kearse
of Florida; and offensive tackle  &UR; Matt Stinchcomb, of Georgia.
</P>
<P>
   The other finalists are Texas A&AMP;M linebacker  &UR; Dat Nguyen, Texas
Tech end  &UR; Montae Reagor and Colorado State guard  &UR; Anthony Cesario.
</P>
<P>
   The finalists will be pared to four on Nov. 6, and the winner
will be announced Dec. 8. Nebraska's  &UR; Grant Wistrom won the award
last season.
</P>
<P>
   Ruegamer also is a candidate for the Outland Award. &QL; 
What's in a name? &QL; 
Notre Dame fullback  &UR; Joey Goodspeed carried only four times in the
game but led all rushers with 109 yards.
</P>
<P>
   But Goodspeed, a 6-foot, 241-pounder, got caught from behind on
his longest run, a 60-yard dash to the ASU 6-yard line.
</P>
<P>
   ``I guess I'm not as fast as I thought,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Hey, the name is Goodspeed, not Greatspeed. &QL; 
A motto is born &QL; 
After the game, safety  &UR; A'Jani Sanders said of the Fighting Irish,
``A team that won't be beat, can't be beat.''
</P>
<P>
   It turns out that's sort of a motto the Irish adopted from
former Coach  &UR; Dan Devine, a Valley resident who once coached at ASU
and later led Notre Dame to a national championship in 1977.
</P>
<P>
   ``I got a note from Coach Devine after we beat Purdue,'' said
Notre Dame Coach  &UR; Bob Davie. ``It said, `An old philosopher once
said that a team that won't be beat, can't be beat. And you just
made an old philosopher very proud. That was one of the greatest
comebacks I've ever seen.'
</P>
<P>
   ``We have kind of adopted that and taken that phrase to
heart.'' &QL; 
Quick hits &QL; 
 &UR; Stephen Trejo, who has been sidelined with a knee sprain, did not
play.
</P>
<P>
   When the power went out at Sun Devil Stadium, the advertisement
that was stuck on the scoreboard was for APS, ``the official power
source for Sun Devil Stadium.''
</P>
<P>
   Notre Dame improved to 24-4 when playing an opponent for the
first time. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
