<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   SHUTTLE-LAUNCH _ Still haven't planned your trip to the Kennedy
Space Center to watch John Glenn's historic space shuttle launch?
Don't expect a front-row seat. Or nearby accommodations. More than
a quarter of a million people are expected to squeeze into a
one-mile area around the space center's Cape Canaveral, Fla., site
to witness the launch, with many more watching from rooftops and
roadsides all over central Florida. Hotel rooms and parking spaces
should be as scarce as Starbucks outlets on the moon. But we
provide tips for watching and lodgings. (Hamilton, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
