</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financings this week is confined to
Tuesday's auction of 3- and 6-month bills and a 52-week bill.
Trading in Treasury securities and on futures on the Chicago Board
of Trade is closed Monday for observance of Columbus Day.
</P>
<P>
   By the close of the New York cash market on Friday, traders
said, the rate on the outstanding 3-month bill was 3.79 percent,
and 3.91 percent on the 6-month bill.. The rate for the 52-week
bill was 3.96 percent.
</P>
