   NEW-SPACECRAFT (Los Angeles) _ The United States is about to
embark on a revival of experimental aircraft and Southern
California's Antelope Valley will play key roles in that effort.
The most visible program in the region is the X-33, a space plane
that will launch next summer to test technology needed for a
reusable spaceship. By Jim Skeen. (Will move in the ``a'' national
and ``n'' California news file.)
