salary increases for top administrators, teachers and other school
employees using money from a $90 million state windfall. Three
board members have stated openly that they are willing to consider
an increase to an already promised 2 percent hike for the nation's
second-largest school district. By Sherry Joe Crosby and Terri
Hardy. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news
file.)
</P>
